---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="How It Works | LG Dryer Repair | Same Day Service | (323) 990-7550"
  description="See exactly how our LG dryer repair process works — from booking to payment. Transparent pricing, OEM parts, same-day service in Los Angeles, Orange County and Ventura County."
>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <div class="hiw-hero">
    <div class="hiw-hero-label">Our process</div>
    <h1>How LG dryer repair works</h1>
    <p>We built our process around one idea: no surprises. You know the price before we start, you approve every step, and you pay only after the dryer is running.</p>
    <div class="hiw-hero-cta">
      <a href="tel:3239907550" class="btn-primary">📞 (323) 990-7550</a>
      <a href="/book/" class="btn-secondary">Book Online</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 6 STEPS DETAILED -->
  <div class="hiw-steps">

    <!-- STEP 1 -->
    <div class="hiw-step-row">
      <div class="hiw-step-bg">01</div>
      <div class="hiw-step-icon">
        <div class="hiw-icon-circle">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <rect x="3" y="5" width="18" height="16" rx="2"/>
            <path d="M16 3v4M8 3v4M3 11h18"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hiw-step-text">
        <div class="hiw-step-label">Step 01</div>
        <h2>Book a visit</h2>
        <p>Booking takes less than 2 minutes. Call us at (323) 990-7550, fill out the booking form on our site, or hit the Call Me Back button and we'll reach out to you — whichever is easiest. We're available to take bookings 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. During booking we'll ask for your address, the LG dryer model if you know it, and a brief description of the problem. We'll then offer you a 2-hour arrival window that works for your schedule. If you're a landlord and won't be on-site, let us know — we'll arrange payment details with you directly so your tenant doesn't have to deal with billing.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- STEP 2 -->
    <div class="hiw-step-row hiw-step-reverse">
      <div class="hiw-step-bg">02</div>
      <div class="hiw-step-icon">
        <div class="hiw-icon-circle">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <path d="M1 16V6a1 1 0 0 1 1-1h11v11"/>
            <path d="M13 8h5l3 4v4h-2"/>
            <circle cx="6.5" cy="17.5" r="2.5"/>
            <circle cx="16.5" cy="17.5" r="2.5"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hiw-step-text">
        <div class="hiw-step-label">Step 02</div>
        <h2>Technician arrives</h2>
        <p>Thirty minutes before our tech leaves for your address, you'll get an automatic text message so you're not left waiting and guessing. We assign a 2-hour arrival window, and our technicians typically arrive in the first 30 minutes of that window. Our tech will arrive in a marked white Ford Transit van in a navy blue uniform. He'll introduce himself, put on shoe covers, and ask you to show him the dryer before he starts.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- STEP 3 -->
    <div class="hiw-step-row">
      <div class="hiw-step-bg">03</div>
      <div class="hiw-step-icon">
        <div class="hiw-icon-circle">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <circle cx="11" cy="11" r="7"/>
            <path d="M21 21l-4.35-4.35"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hiw-step-text">
        <div class="hiw-step-label">Step 03</div>
        <h2>Diagnosis ($65)</h2>
        <p>The diagnostic fee is $65 and covers a full inspection of your LG dryer — electrical, mechanical, venting, and error codes. This is not a guessing-game visit. By the end of the diagnosis, our tech will tell you exactly what's wrong, which part needs replacing if any, and give you a complete written estimate covering parts and labor. The $65 fee is waived entirely if you approve the repair and we proceed. If you decide not to go ahead with the repair for any reason, you pay the $65 and that's it — no hard feelings, no pressure.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- STEP 4 -->
    <div class="hiw-step-row hiw-step-reverse">
      <div class="hiw-step-bg">04</div>
      <div class="hiw-step-icon">
        <div class="hiw-icon-circle">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/>
            <path d="M8 12l3 3 5-6"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hiw-step-text">
        <div class="hiw-step-label">Step 04</div>
        <h2>You approve the quote</h2>
        <p>Nothing happens until you say yes. Once you approve the estimate, our tech will either begin the repair immediately (if the part is on the truck) or arrange a return visit to complete the work. We never start a repair, order a part, or charge anything beyond the diagnostic fee without your explicit approval. This step is the most important one — it's where we earn your trust.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- STEP 5 -->
    <div class="hiw-step-row">
      <div class="hiw-step-bg">05</div>
      <div class="hiw-step-icon">
        <div class="hiw-icon-circle">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <path d="M14.7 6.3a4 4 0 0 0-5.4 5.4L3 18l3 3 6.3-6.3a4 4 0 0 0 5.4-5.4l-2.5 2.5-2.5-2.5 2.5-2.5z"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hiw-step-text">
        <div class="hiw-step-label">Step 05</div>
        <h2>Repair completed</h2>
        <p>We stock the most common LG dryer parts on every truck — thermal fuses, heating elements, drum rollers, belts, igniters, and more. In 85% of visits the repair is completed the same day, often within the same visit as the diagnosis. We use only genuine OEM LG parts. Our supplier relationships mean we often source parts at prices lower than retail, and we pass that savings on to you. If a part needs to be ordered, we collect a prepayment equal to the cost of the part, order it immediately, and schedule a return visit as soon as it arrives — usually the next morning.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- STEP 6 -->
    <div class="hiw-step-row hiw-step-reverse">
      <div class="hiw-step-bg">06</div>
      <div class="hiw-step-icon">
        <div class="hiw-icon-circle">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <rect x="2" y="5" width="20" height="14" rx="2"/>
            <path d="M2 10h20M6 15h4"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hiw-step-text">
        <div class="hiw-step-label">Step 06</div>
        <h2>Payment after demonstration</h2>
        <p>Before we ask for payment, the tech will run your dryer through a full cycle and show you that the problem is resolved. Only once you confirm that everything is working as it should do we process payment. We accept all major payment methods: credit and debit cards, cash, Zelle, Venmo, PayPal, and checks. For landlords who arranged remote payment at booking — we'll charge the agreed method on file. Every repair comes with a 1-year parts and labor warranty.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <div class="hiw-faq">
    <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>

    <div class="hiw-faq-item">
      <div class="hiw-faq-q">What if I decline the repair after diagnosis?</div>
      <div class="hiw-faq-a">You pay the $65 diagnostic fee and nothing else. No obligation, no pressure. We'll email you the diagnosis report so you have it on file.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="hiw-faq-item">
      <div class="hiw-faq-q">Do you charge extra if a part needs to be ordered?</div>
      <div class="hiw-faq-a">No extra fees for ordering. You prepay the cost of the part, we order it through our suppliers — often at a price lower than you'd find at retail — and schedule a return visit. Labor is billed at the second visit.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="hiw-faq-item">
      <div class="hiw-faq-q">What does the 2-hour window mean exactly?</div>
      <div class="hiw-faq-a">When you book, we give you a 2-hour arrival window — for example 10am–12pm. Our technician will text you 30 minutes before he leaves, and in most cases arrives in the first half of that window. We do our best to respect your time.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="hiw-faq-item">
      <div class="hiw-faq-q">I'm a landlord and won't be at the property. How does that work?</div>
      <div class="hiw-faq-a">No problem — we handle landlord situations regularly. During booking, provide a card or other payment method on file. Our tech will coordinate access with your tenant, complete the repair, and charge your payment method directly. You'll receive a full report by email.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- BOTTOM CTA -->
  <div class="hiw-bottom-cta">
    <h2>Ready to schedule?</h2>
    <p>Same-day service available in Los Angeles, Orange County, and Ventura County.</p>
    <div class="hiw-cta-buttons">
      <a href="tel:3239907550" class="btn-primary">📞 (323) 990-7550</a>
      <a href="/book/" class="btn-secondary">Book Online</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What if I decline the repair after diagnosis?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "You pay the $65 diagnostic fee and nothing else. No obligation, no pressure. We'll email you the diagnosis report so you have it on file."}
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do you charge extra if a part needs to be ordered?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "No extra fees for ordering. You prepay the cost of the part, we order it through our suppliers — often at a price lower than retail — and schedule a return visit. Labor is billed at the second visit."}
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What does the 2-hour window mean exactly?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "When you book, we give you a 2-hour arrival window — for example 10am–12pm. Our technician will text you 30 minutes before he leaves, and in most cases arrives in the first half of that window."}
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "I'm a landlord and won't be at the property. How does that work?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "No problem — we handle landlord situations regularly. During booking, provide a card or other payment method on file. Our tech will coordinate access with your tenant, complete the repair, and charge your payment method directly. You'll receive a full report by email."}
      }
    ]
  })} />

</Layout>

<style>
  .hiw-hero {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 60px auto 80px;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 0 24px;
  }

  .hiw-hero-label {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: #1a6cf6;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .hiw-hero h1 {
    font-size: 2.2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #ffffff;
    margin: 0 0 20px 0;
  }

  .hiw-hero p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: #c8d0dc;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0 0 32px 0;
  }

  .hiw-hero-cta {
    display: flex;
    gap: 16px;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    background: #1a6cf6;
    color: #ffffff;
    padding: 14px 32px;
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .btn-secondary {
    background: transparent;
    color: #1a6cf6;
    padding: 14px 32px;
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid #1a6cf6;
  }

  .hiw-steps {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 24px 80px;
  }

  .hiw-step-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 48px;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 64px;
    position: relative;
  }

  .hiw-step-reverse .hiw-step-icon {
    order: 2;
  }

  .hiw-step-bg {
    position: absolute;
    font-size: 8rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: rgba(26, 108, 246, 0.06);
    top: -20px;
    left: -20px;
    line-height: 1;
    pointer-events: none;
    user-select: none;
  }

  .hiw-step-icon {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .hiw-icon-circle {
    width: 120px;
    height: 120px;
    background: rgba(26, 108, 246, 0.08);
    border-radius: 50%;
    border: 1px solid rgba(26, 108, 246, 0.2);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .hiw-icon-circle svg {
    width: 48px;
    height: 48px;
    stroke: #1a6cf6;
    fill: none;
    stroke-width: 1.2;
    stroke-linecap: round;
    stroke-linejoin: round;
  }

  .hiw-step-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: #1a6cf6;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .hiw-step-text h2 {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #ffffff;
    margin: 0 0 12px 0;
  }

  .hiw-step-text p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: #c8d0dc;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .hiw-faq {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 24px 80px;
  }

  .hiw-faq h2 {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #ffffff;
    margin: 0 0 32px 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .hiw-faq-item {
    border-top: 1px solid #1e2a3a;
    padding: 20px 0;
  }

  .hiw-faq-q {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #ffffff;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .hiw-faq-a {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #c8d0dc;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .hiw-bottom-cta {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 60px 24px;
    border-top: 1px solid #1e2a3a;
    margin-top: 40px;
  }

  .hiw-bottom-cta h2 {
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #ffffff;
    margin: 0 0 12px 0;
  }

  .hiw-bottom-cta p {
    color: #8a9ab0;
    margin: 0 0 32px 0;
  }

  .hiw-cta-buttons {
    display: flex;
    gap: 16px;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hiw-step-row {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 24px;
    }

    .hiw-step-reverse .hiw-step-icon {
      order: 0;
    }

    .hiw-hero h1 {
      font-size: 1.7rem;
    }
  }
</style>
